Mediobanca closes mark zero bond early . Italian investment bank Mediobanca said it had closed its 10 - year , 150 million mark zero coupon bond on the first day of issue due to over - demand . It said in a statement the offer had been closed at midday " because total demand largely exceeded the amount on offer . " The issue , the first Italian domestic bond in marks , had been due to be on public offer for two days from Tuesday . The " Mediobanca Zero Coupon 1996 - 2006 " , issued in a single denomination of 5 , 000 marks at 56 . 30 percent , will be repaid at par on November 9 , 2006 . Gross annual yield is 5 . 91 percent . - - Milan newsroom + 392 66129589 
